<DrugInformationSummary id="CDR0000769544"><DrugInfoMetaData><DrugInfoType Combination="Yes">Brief</DrugInfoType><DrugInfoAudience>Patients</DrugInfoAudience><DrugInfoDescription>This combination contains the chemotherapy drugs etoposide phosphate, vincristine sulfate (Oncovin), cyclophosphamide,  and doxorubicin hydrochloride (hydroxydaunomycin), the targeted therapy drug rituximab, and the steroid hormone prednisone. Combinations usually work better than single drugs because 
         different drugs kill 
         cancer 
         cells in different ways.</DrugInfoDescription><DrugInfoURL xref="https://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/drugs/R-EPOCH">R-EPOCH</DrugInfoURL><TerminologyLink ref="CDR0000768572">R-EPOCH regimen</TerminologyLink><GlossaryLink ref="CDR0000768581">R-EPOCH</GlossaryLink><PronunciationInfo><MediaLink ref="CDR0000798011" type="audio/mpeg" alt="" language="en" id="_3"/></PronunciationInfo></DrugInfoMetaData><DrugInfoTitle>R-EPOCH</DrugInfoTitle><Section id="_1">                                                              
