  <Para id="_4">Each of the drugs in this combination is approved by the 
         <GlossaryTermRef href="CDR0000454785" dictionary="Cancer.gov" audience="Patient">Food and Drug 
         Administration (FDA)</GlossaryTermRef> 
         to treat cancer or conditions related to cancer.</Para>
 </Section><Section id="_5">
  <Title>Use in Cancer</Title>
  <Para id="_6">R-EPOCH 
         is used to treat:</Para>
  <ItemizedList Style="bullet" id="_9"><ListItem><Strong><GlossaryTermRef href="CDR0000444967" dictionary="Cancer.gov" audience="Patient">B-cell</GlossaryTermRef> <GlossaryTermRef href="CDR0000045148" dictionary="Cancer.gov" audience="Patient">non-Hodgkin lymphoma</GlossaryTermRef>.</Strong></ListItem></ItemizedList>
  <Para id="_8">This combination may also be used with other drugs or 
         treatments or to treat other types of cancer. It is being studied in the treatment of <GlossaryTermRef href="CDR0000270800" dictionary="Cancer.gov" audience="Patient">Hodgkin lymphoma</GlossaryTermRef> and <GlossaryTermRef href="CDR0000543504" dictionary="Cancer.gov" audience="Patient">B-cell acute leukemia</GlossaryTermRef>.</Para>
